DAWALT v. COMMONWEALTH (Decided January 14, 1930.) F. A. ¡Harrison for movant.

Commonwealth.

J. W. Cammack, Attorney General, and Douglas C. Vest for the PER CURIAM.

Judgment of conviction for violation of the prohibition law, imposing a fine of $100 and 30 days in jail.

Appeal denied. Judgment affirmed.
